The present study was conducted to evaluate the combined effect of low-dose 
gamma irradiation and antimicrobial coating on the shelf life of pre-cooked 
shrimp (Penaeus spp.). Antimicrobial coatings were obtained by incorporating 
various concentrations of thyme oil and trans-cinnamaldehyde in coating 
formulations prepared from soy or whey protein isolates. Coated shrimps were 
stored at 4 +/- 1 degrees C under aerobic conditions and were periodically 
evaluated for aerobic plate counts (APCs) and Pseudomonas putida. Sensory 
